{"id":14882021,"mediaExerciseId":"c4b5e43e-35aa-4e22-9628-ed3ced5e5462","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"27","chapterTitle":"Leasing","groupId":612532,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":910,"solutions":[{"id":6505204,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"\nThe objective of the assignment is to explain the reasons that motivate a company to be a lessor rather than a lender. \n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"As we learned at the beginning of the chapter, many companies are in the business of acquiring the assets that other companies need to use to lease to them; in some cases, the producing companies themselves have created captive finance companies to lease their products.\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"But ***what are the benefits for a company to acquire assets to lease them later?***\n\nThe emphasis in this section is on **the use of tax benefits granted to the asset owner such as depreciation and debt financing**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"81965c42-87a7-42c2-b9a0-b20ed2cf22d9","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":tr